definition: Ba state during Zhou dynasty (in east of modern Sichuan)/abbr. for east Sichuan or Chongqing/surname Ba/abbr. for Palestine or Palestinian/abbr. for Pakistan

to long for/to wish/to cling to/to stick to/sth that sticks/close to/next to/spread open/informal abbr. for bus 巴士[ba1 shi4]/bar (unit of pressure)/nominalizing suffix on certain nouns, such as 尾巴[wei3 ba5], tail

sentences.english: A man pulls up an anchor line in Al Aqabah Harbor, Jordan.

sentences.english: An ancient country of Palestine between the Dead Sea and the Gulf of Aqaba .
sentences.chinese: 巴勒斯坦的一個古國，位於死海與亞喀巴灣之間。

sentences.english: The Gulf of Suez and the Gulf of Aqaba extend from the Red Sea toward the Mediterranean.

sentences.english: There is also the Dead Sea, and Aqaba , where we have an incredible Coral Reef!
